## DOMAIN 4 — MULTI-SOURCE COMPARISON & MATCHING

### Comparison Workflow

When comparing two datasets (Sheet A = source/master, Sheet B = new/import):

**Step 1 — Configuration:**
- Identify best match columns: prioritize email > ID > phone > full name > org name
- Set fuzzy threshold (default 0.82, lower for noisy data)
- Decide normalization pre-processing (strip phone digits, lowercase email, etc.)

**Step 2 — Exact Match Pass:**
- Normalize all match column values
- Build hashmap from Sheet A
- Scan Sheet B, pop matched A records from pool
- O(n) complexity

**Step 3 — Fuzzy Match Pass:**
- Only on unmatched rows from both sheets
- Compute composite similarity score
- Best-match assignment (not greedy — prevent double-matching)

**Step 4 — Categorize Results:**

| Category | Meaning | Action |
|---|---|---|
| **Exact Match** | Record in B confirmed in A | Safe to import/sync |
| **Fuzzy Match** | Record in B likely in A (with differences) | Review field-level differences |
| **Only in A** | Record exists in master, not in import | Investigate: deleted? missed? |
| **Only in B** | New record not in master | Add to master after validation |
| **Duplicate in B** | Import file has internal duplicates | Deduplicate import first |
| **Duplicate in A** | Master has internal duplicates | Clean master before merging |

**Step 5 — Field-Level Diff (for fuzzy matches):**
- For each matched pair, highlight individual field differences
- Show: field name | value in A | value in B | similarity score
- Let user pick which value to keep per field

### Common Comparison Scenarios

**Scenario: CRM → Event Import reconciliation**
- Match on: email (primary) + full name (secondary)
- Expect: typos in names, phone format differences, org name variations
- Watch for: same email + different name = possible name change or data error

**Scenario: Master list vs. vendor export**
- Match on: ID (if available) + email fallback
- Expect: different field naming conventions, different date formats
- Watch for: IDs that exist in vendor but not in master = new records to investigate

**Scenario: Database migration validation**
- Match on: primary key
- All records should be exact matches
- Any non-match = migration error
- Any record only in old = not migrated
- Any record only in new = incorrectly created

