## DOMAIN 5 — SCHEMA DETECTION & TYPE INFERENCE

### Column Type Detection Rules

```
Check column name patterns FIRST, then validate with value content.

Name pattern → Type:
  /email/i                  → email
  /phone|tel|mobile|fax/i   → phone
  /date|time|_at$|dob/i     → date
  /url|link|website/i       → url
  /amount|price|cost|revenue|salary|value/i → currency
  /zip|postal/i             → zip
  /city/i                   → city
  /state|province/i         → state
  /country/i                → country
  /address|street/i         → address
  /first.?name/i            → firstName
  /last.?name/i             → lastName
  /^name$|full.?name/i      → fullName
  /org|company|business|account/i → organization
  /status|type|source|category/i  → category
  /^id$|_id$|uuid/i         → id

Value content analysis (sample 50 rows):
  All numeric          → number
  All valid emails     → email
  All parseable dates  → date
  All URL patterns     → url
  Unique ratio ≤ 10%   → category (low-cardinality)
  Boolean pattern      → boolean
  Default              → text
```

### Primary Key Detection

A column is likely a primary key if:
- All values are non-null
- Uniqueness ratio = 1.0 (no duplicates)
- Column name matches `/^id$|_id$|uuid|key/i`
- OR it is the first column with all unique values

