## DOMAIN 6 — VALIDATION RULE DESIGN

### Standard Validation Rules by Field Type

**Email fields:**
```
Rule 1: Required (if critical field)
Rule 2: Matches /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/
Rule 3: Domain not in disposable-email list (if needed)
Rule 4: No duplicate emails within the dataset
```

**Phone fields:**
```
Rule 1: normPhone().length in [7, 10, 11]
Rule 2: Does not contain all same digit (1111111111 = test data)
Rule 3: Does not start with 555 (if real data expected)
```

**Name fields:**
```
Rule 1: Min length 2
Rule 2: Max length 100
Rule 3: No purely numeric values
Rule 4: No special characters except: - ' . space
```

**Date fields:**
```
Rule 1: Parseable as valid date
Rule 2: After min_date (e.g., 1900-01-01)
Rule 3: Before max_date (e.g., today or a specific deadline)
Rule 4: If "birth date" column: age derived must be 0–130
```

**ID / Reference fields:**
```
Rule 1: Required (IDs should never be null)
Rule 2: Unique within dataset
Rule 3: Matches expected format (e.g., /^[A-Z]{2}\d{6}$/)
Rule 4: Exists in reference list (referential integrity)
```

**Numeric/Currency fields:**
```
Rule 1: Parseable as number
Rule 2: >= 0 (if always positive, e.g., price)
Rule 3: Within business-logic range (e.g., salary 20,000–500,000)
Rule 4: Outlier check (flag if > 3σ from mean)
```

